case.sTitle: "Loading" spinner never goes away for EMPTY data set in CGP

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Bill Heitzeg by Ping Kho

event.s:
Discovered when testing CGP with CCR.2012.03 (Cathy) on QA2 server with sml01-fat db (192.168.16.251:7001).
Repro Steps: (1a) Precondition: CGP contains empty data set; this could possibly be reproduced by refreshing sml01-fat db, migrating it, then refresh the SQL-DB Jenkins job; let data be ETL'ed over.
(1b) From DB server, CCR log will show something like: 2012-11-26 17:04:44,885 [12] INFO CCR.Core.CCRLogger - SSIS Package execution result for Small Practice: Failure 2012-11-26 17:04:44,886 [12] WARN CCR.Core.CCRLogger - >[-1073548784]: Executing the query "merge [patient_rule_war] as p using [patient_rule..." failed with the following error: "The MERGE statement attempted to UPDATE or DELETE the same row more than once. This happens when a target row matches more than one source row. A MERGE statement cannot UPDATE/DELETE the same row of the target table multiple times. Refine the ON clause to ensure a target row matches at most one source row, or use the GROUP BY clause to group the source rows.". Possible failure reasons: Problems with the query, "ResultSet" property not set correctly, parameters not set correctly, or connection not established correctly.
(2) Go to CGP, and the "spinner" seems to be spinning forever, when CGP contains empty data set.
----
Proposed fix: When there's no data to be displayed on CGP (or on ER), spinner/loading image should go away.
event.sChanges: Tester changed from (None) to Ping Kho Milestone changed from 'CCR.2012.04.01 (Dwight): 11/21/2012' to 'Defect Queue'.
event.sHtml:
Discovered when testing CGP with CCR.2012.03 (Cathy) on QA2 server  with sml01-fat db (192.168.16.251:7001).

Repro Steps:
(1a) Precondition: CGP contains empty data set; this could possibly be reproduced by refreshing sml01-fat db, migrating it, then refresh the SQL-DB Jenkins job; let data be ETL'ed over.

(1b) From DB server, CCR log will show something like:
2012-11-26 17:04:44,885 [12] INFO  CCR.Core.CCRLogger - SSIS Package execution result for Small Practice: Failure
2012-11-26 17:04:44,886 [12] WARN  CCR.Core.CCRLogger - >[-1073548784]: Executing the query "merge [patient_rule_war] as p
using [patient_rule..." failed with the following error: "The MERGE statement attempted to UPDATE or DELETE the same row more than once. This happens when a target row matches more than one source row. A MERGE statement cannot UPDATE/DELETE the same row of the target table multiple times. Refine the ON clause to ensure a target row matches at most one source row, or use the GROUP BY clause to group the source rows.". Possible failure reasons: Problems with the query, "ResultSet" property not set correctly, parameters not set correctly, or connection not established correctly.


(2) Go to CGP, and the "spinner" seems to be spinning forever, when CGP contains empty data set.

----

Proposed fix:
When there's no data to be displayed on CGP (or on ER), spinner/loading image should go away.

event.s:
Tested on 192.168.16.175:7102 on FF (Py: 3842,Core: 120374,CM: 118111,ER: 120374). Ticket failed QA for the following scenario -
The next due date is shown as tomorrow's date when the service 'CMPD' that satisfies guideline 'Consider enrollment in CM' is added via the Services page. The 'Next Due' date is fine when the guideline is statused as 'Done' from the encounter form.
Repro -
1) Add service 'CMPE' via the Service page for a patient.
2) Schedule an appt for today and generate encounter. Prompt 'Consider enrollment in CM' is seen.
3) DO NOT status the prompt as 'Done' on the nec. form. Instead,go to the Services page for this patient and add the service 'CMPD' manually.
4) Come back to the encounter form and open Patient History.
BUG - Prompt 'Consider enrollment in CM' displays the 'Next Due' date as tomorrow's date. If you modify the above step (3) and status the prompt as 'Done' directly from the encounter form,then the 'Next Due' date on patient history is correct.

Tested on 192.168.16.175:7102 on FF (Py: 3842,Core: 120374,CM: 118111,ER: 120374). Ticket failed QA for the following scenario -

The next due date is shown as tomorrow's date when the service 'CMPD' that satisfies guideline 'Consider enrollment in CM' is added via the Services page. The 'Next Due' date is fine when the guideline is statused as 'Done' from the encounter form.

Repro -

1) Add service 'CMPE' via the Service page for a patient.

2) Schedule an appt for today and generate encounter. Prompt 'Consider enrollment in CM' is seen.

3) DO NOT status the prompt as 'Done' on the nec. form. Instead,go to the Services page for this patient and add the service 'CMPD' manually.

4) Come back to the encounter form and open Patient History.

BUG - Prompt 'Consider enrollment in CM' displays the 'Next Due' date as tomorrow's date. If you modify the above step (3) and status the prompt as 'Done' directly from the encounter form,then the 'Next Due' date on patient history is correct.

case.sTitle: Resources

event.s: As a care manager, I would like to have quick access to a list of resources in my patient's area to which I can refer my patient.
event.sHtml: As a care manager, I would like to have quick access to a list of resources in my patient's area to which I can refer my patient.

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Chaney Coleman by Allison Thannisch

event.s:
This is a list of resources that the Care Manager may call on for the patient. Ex. - Transportation - Food Education - Weight Watchers - Physical Trainer
May want to mark items and provide them to the patient.
These should be provided by the member so that we can tailor the list. Need the format of the list.
Want to be able to print out or type a note for the patient. Map may be out of scope for the first implementation.
Could just provide a way to render the list of resouces within an i-frame as a simplistic first step. This could be with an Excelspreadsheet as a simple way to start.
event.sHtml:
This is a list of resources that the Care Manager may call on for the patient.
Ex.
- Transportation
- Food Education
- Weight Watchers
- Physical Trainer

May want to mark items and provide them to the patient.

These should be provided by the member so that we can tailor the list. Need the format of the list.

Want to be able to print out or type a note for the patient. Map may be out of scope for the first implementation.

Could just provide a way to render the list of resouces within an i-frame as a simplistic first step. This could be with an Excelspreadsheet as a simple way to start.

case.sTitle: Care Management Lists Grid: Care manager specific search should not return patients care manager has touched

event.s:
STORY:
As a care manager I want to see my worklist by filtering for all patients assigned to me.
Requirements:
Patients that the care manager has touched but are not assigned to the care manager should not display in the Care Management Lists grid when the user filters the grid by a specific care manager.
Patients that are assigned to the care manger through a care plan or have an appointment with that care manger are the only patients that should display.
event.sHtml:
STORY:

As a care manager I want to see my worklist by filtering for all patients assigned to me.

 

Requirements:

Patients that the care manager has touched but are not assigned to the care manager should not display in the Care Management Lists grid when the user filters the grid by a specific care manager.

Patients that are assigned to the care manger through a care plan or have an appointment with that care manger are the only patients that should display.

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Bill Heitzeg by Allison Thannisch

case.sTitle: NEW: CM | Notes flyout <Signed> the Encounter and Action Plan page <Save> should be disabled

event.s:
STEPS: 1. CM | go through Action Plan page. <SAVE> 2. Notes flyout 3. <Sign> 4. goto Action Plan page. 4. add notes "test 1" 5. <Save>
RESULT: page is still editable.
EXPECTED: After signed, the encounter should be locked.
1.<Save> <Save & Continue> related Buttons to be disabled in Encounter and Action Plan.
From Nate: Encounter notes is <Signed> in Notes flyout, is the user allowed to update the patient note in the Action page to the Note slide out and chicklet? The “save” buttons on each page should be disabled if the note is signed (signed date on cm_encounter object is not null). Also, the patient note on the Action Plan page should probably be read only at that point.
From Sarah Neyaz: When a note is Signed – it is then locked and cannot be editable on any page or any form. There is no way to 'unlock' the note.
If there is another encounter with the patient it would have a new note. A New Encounter would have another scheduled appointment associated with it and a new note associated with that.

event.s:
Use Case
As a care manager, I would like the ability to select self management goals for a patient from a pre-defined list. I would also like the ability to add self management goals to a patient's chart on the fly and not be constrained by the per-defined self management goals.
Requirements
Free text goals will be saved to the patient's record
Free text goals will not persist across the user's session. Meaning if the user entered a free-text self management goal of walking up the stairs for Patient A, if the user then wanted to enter this same goal for Patient B, it would not be in their list to select from, they would have to free-text this in again.
...more to come
Attaching Sarah's images
event.sHtml:
Use Case

As a care manager, I would like the ability to select self management goals for a patient from a pre-defined list. I would also like the ability to add self management goals to a patient's chart on the fly and not be constrained by the per-defined self management goals.

Requirements

  • Free text goals will be saved to the patient's record
  • Free text goals will not persist across the user's session. Meaning if the user entered a free-text self management goal of walking up the stairs for Patient A, if the user then wanted to enter this same goal for Patient B, it would not be in their list to select from, they would have to free-text this in again.
  • ...more to come

Attaching Sarah's images

case.sTitle: Encounter Page: Follow Up - not required field

event.s:
STORY: As a care manager, I do not want to be forced to have a follow up scheduled for my patient in order to save their encounter note.
Requirement: Follow up should not be required in order to save the encounter.
* If the patient is not enrolled in a care plan, the follow up should default to blank.
* User should be able to clear out a defaulted follow up date

Thank you for the clarification Emi.
This needs to be fixed, see my comments below
When I think about what valid outcomes are (ticket 50336 still needs to be implemented to fix this) I am trying to figure out if any would have units that are not obvious. The one that jumps out at me is 'weight' since this could be in kg or lbs and the unit of measure would be needed.
The question is should this hold up the 09 release...I guess not. Moving to Care Management
Valid Outcomes (per case 50336):
Blood Pressure
BMI
Creatinine Clearance
Ejection Fraction
Hemoglobin A1C
LDL
Peak Flow
Weight

  • LDL
  • Peak Flow
  • Weight

case.sTitle: P09: CM| Lists page redraw page load takes a long time in IE7 and 8. Perf issue

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Nate Wetzel by Emi Brown

event.s:
Performance issue: 8 - 17 sec to display all the page when you select a new patient. Sent mail to Sarah and Faqir to confirm machine/perf guidelines for page loads.
Steps: 1. http://ccrtest.affirmaconsulting.com CM| scroll down, clicking on the Patient Name "small down arrow widget" to the left of the Patient name. 2. See that 3 menu choices appear. | Schedule Patient| Enroll | Start Encounter | 3. click on Enroll or Encounter 4. count how much it takes for the page to finish loading.
RESULT: opens Enroll page - waiting on redraw 8 sec to display the vertical tabs to finish the page load on WXP SP2 IE7 machine.
First time opening Encounter page, redraw took about 13-16 sec.
Repro Machine environment: IE7. Toshiba Windows XP Tablet PC edition Intel Celeron M processor 1.4 GHz. 496 MB RAM Wired connection at 1.0Gbps
WIth IE9 COre i5 - 2430M CPU @ 2.4Ghz, RAM 4GB OSWin7 64 bit IBM thinkpad, took about 5 sec load time with a new patient.
Note: Need performance guidelines from PM/UE with machine spec requirement guidelines.
_____________________________________________________ Bug 2:
1. http://ccrtest.affirmaconsulting.com CM| scroll down, clicking on the Patient Name "small down arrow widget" to the left of the Patient name. 2. See that 3 menu choices appear. | Schedule Patient| Enroll | Start Encounter | 3. click on Enroll or Encounter 4. count how much it takes for the page to finish loading. 5. go back to Lists nav by clicking on the CM|Lists. 6. start counting.
perf issue: Page load is slow coming from CPE - back to LIsts page. 18 sec to finish the page load on WXP SP2 IE7 machine.

event.s:
(Andy)
1) Bring up main CCR Page
http://ccr-dev-app03.devid.local/CCRCareManagement/Lists
2) Select a patient, and select Enroll
3) Select Add More Self-Management goals, and select a goal
4) Click in Plan Target field. - Notice flashing cursor
5) Attempt to add data to Plan Target field

Either the user should be able to add data, or they shouldn't be allowed to click within the txt box.

Field appears to be editable, but user can not input data.

case.sTitle: CM | Encounter | sparklines spec change per Sarah 1)move outcome result to right of sparkline.2) remove baseline

event.s:
STEPS: CM | select Gorden, Max goto Encounter | see Outcomes| Echo - Target is "15" Achived is "20"
From Sarah Neyaz: Consider Fix for Sparkline: 1) Take the horizontal base line out
2) can we move the date and outcome result to the right of the sparkline? Both of those elements are taking up a lot of useful real estate where we could instead expand the sparklines and give more vertical space to the data points. I can talk to Chris King and try to put this into an iteration within the cleanup section.
_________________________________________________________ Details on the sparkline spec from the e-mail 8/29/2012: Hi Sarah, I would like a CM sparkline spec behavior clarification since there has been numerous bugs around CM sparklines. I think it will be helpful. (JFYI, attached is patient status flyout mock up from long time ago.) I wanted to clarify the behavior of sparklines in CM since there have been numerous bug fixes and behavior regressions. Others feel free to chime in. Thanks!
QUESTIONS: Sparkline : Mouse over on dot: On hover of the dots, the data should display e.g. On hover of weight dot 1: 90 lbs, on hover of weight dot 2: 98lbs etc. if goal has not been achieved the goal amount e.g. 90lbs should display in red color; otherwise it should just be in the default black text. (for some reason all hover over text displaying in red currently)
Color of the dot changes: yes, if target is achieved dot = green, if target not achieved dot = red. If the dot is achieved: If the dot is not achieved target: Action Plan sparkline dots: Mouse over: on mouseover on the DOT (everywhere), the dot should be black so the user gets visual feedback that that dot is being hovered on. BP sparkline dots: Shows 2 lines,
Dots dots: Triangle dots: eNot sure where the triangle dots came from – is this to distinguish diastolic vs systolic? Color change upon mouse over : if target is achieved dot = green, if target not achieved dot = red.
Baseline Horizontal line: Take this horizontal line out, we are not going to have this as it is visually difficult to understand the target (baseline) in such a small space. See general suggestion above on gaining more vertical real estate for sparklines. Representing?
Date on the score: Date that the vital/outcome was taken. Any Difference on UI like Encounter page, Patient Status(History) sparkline behaviors/ UI. All the same. _______________________________________________________________________ Background info: The reason for this ask is because we just opened a bug: found by Nate. https://fogbugz.devid.local/default.asp?47929
Build: rev 111749 build #145 http://192.168.16.178/patient/# all browsers. Found by Nate Wetzel.
STEPS: CM | select Gorden, Max goto Encounter | see Outcomes| Echo - Target is "15" Achived is "20" see on sparkline, score "20" mouse over sparkline dot.
RESULT: mouse over shows "Score 15"
Expected: (Nate, please revise if it's different since the sparkline specs has been not so clear due to numerous regression bugs...) 1) mouse over to show "Score 20" 2) Horizontal grey line should indicate the baseline of the Target score so it should be lined up at "15" relative to the dot value Clarification will be helpful.
To make it easier to sort the Fogbugz CM sparkline bugs, I will be putting Tags: “CMsparklines”as I find them. Thanks.

case.sTitle: CM | Plan Setup | Outcomes Labs/Services input allowed characters / similar to Encounter | Outcomes | New Target - Spec issue

event.s:
Labs and services can be entered in many different ways
Result: Do we need to allow for more flexibility in entering data in Targets? Currently, CM | Encounter | Outcomes | New Target allow only numerics. And we have BP bug 36731 for allowing "/"
Suggestion/ Need PM feedback: 1) Need same input/error handling as in the same input in CM | Encounter | Outcomes | New Target input box.
2) Need data for how these are entered in the hospital setting and possibly need to allow: ' (height) F (temp) C (temp) cm (head circumference) % (Asthma result) r= (Asthma result) P> (Asthma result) ><=+- (Asthma result or other results) , (comma for separating two entries for Asthma test results) . (decimal)
And have error handling logic accordingly. _______________________________________________________________ As an example, I listed out the vitals from the Plan setup page: Vitals| US/ Metric Blood Pressure 130/56 Height 5'5 164cm Weight kg lbs Pulse Temperature 98.5 F 34.5C BMI Respiration Head Circumference 56cm (measured in babies?) LDL screening Hemoglobin A1C Diabetic Foot Exam Diabetic Eye Exam UMA EKG Echo Creatinine Pneumovax Flu Vaccine ACE/ARB Beta Blocker
Example of an Asthma Control Test: ACT was 0.85 (baseline) Responsiveness of the ACT to changes in asthma control and lung function was demonstrated with significant correlations between changes in ACT scores and changes in specialists' ratings (r=0.44, P<.001), ACQ scores (r=-0.69, P<.001), and percent predicted FEV1 values (r=0.29, P<.001). An ACT score of 19 or less provided optimum balance of sensitivity (71%) and specificity (71%) for detecting uncontrolled asthma.
NOTE: Related to Blood pressure BUG: 36731
event.sHtml:
Labs and services can be entered in many different ways

Result:
Do we need to allow for more flexibility in entering data in Targets?
Currently, CM | Encounter | Outcomes | New Target allow only numerics. And we have BP bug 36731 for allowing "/"

Suggestion/ Need PM feedback:
1) Need same input/error handling as in the same input in CM | Encounter | Outcomes | New Target input box.

2) Need data for how these are entered in the hospital setting and possibly need to allow:
'  (height)
F (temp)
C (temp)
cm (head circumference)
%  (Asthma result)
r= (Asthma result)
P> (Asthma result)
><=+-  (Asthma result or other results)
,  (comma for separating two entries for Asthma test results)
. (decimal)

And have error handling logic accordingly.
_______________________________________________________________
As an example, I listed out the vitals from the Plan setup page:
Vitals|  US/ Metric
Blood Pressure  130/56 
Height  5'5 164cm
Weight  kg lbs
Pulse   
Temperature  98.5 F 34.5C
BMI   
Respiration   
Head Circumference  56cm (measured in babies?)
LDL screening   
Hemoglobin A1C   
Diabetic Foot Exam   
Diabetic Eye Exam   
UMA   
EKG   
Echo   
Creatinine   
Pneumovax   
Flu Vaccine   
ACE/ARB   
Beta Blocker     

Example of an Asthma Control Test: ACT was 0.85 (baseline)
Responsiveness of the ACT to changes in asthma control and lung function was demonstrated with significant correlations between changes in ACT scores and changes in specialists' ratings (r=0.44, P<.001), ACQ scores (r=-0.69, P<.001), and percent predicted FEV1 values (r=0.29, P<.001). An ACT score of 19 or less provided optimum balance of sensitivity (71%) and specificity (71%) for detecting uncontrolled asthma.


NOTE: Related to Blood pressure BUG:
36731

case.sTitle: CM - Care Planning Enrollment - page level error handling

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Faqir Ahmed by Sarah Neyaz

event.s:
On field level errors e.g. missing fields there should not be a popup for each error - there should be field level errors displaying. The field in error should be highlighted in red and a message should display below "Required field"
Check out "error" (field level) on CrUX
http://192.168.16.58/CrUX/boilerplate
Attached is a mockup of the field level error handling. For each field that is in error that field should be highlighted all at once. If there are 3 errors on the page all 3 of those fields should be highlighted in red with the appropriate message in red: #ff0000 appear.

Got clarification from Sarah on the sparklines. entered another bug 48085 as for https://fogbugz.devid.local/default.asp?48085  can we move the date and outcome result to the right of the sparkline? Both of those elements are taking up a lot of useful real estate where we could instead expand the sparklines and give more vertical space to the data points. I can talk to Chris King and try to put this into an iteration within the cleanup section.  Baseline Horizontal line: Take this horizontal line out, we are not going to have this as it is visually difficult to understand the target (baseline) in such a small space. ____________________________________________________________
UPDATED SPARKLINE SPEC per Sarah Neyaz from e-mail.:
Hi Sarah, I would like a CM sparkline spec behavior clarification since there has been numerous bugs around CM sparklines. I think it will be helpful. (JFYI, attached is patient status flyout mock up from long time ago.) I wanted to clarify the behavior of sparklines in CM since there have been numerous bug fixes and behavior regressions. Others feel free to chime in. Thanks!
QUESTIONS: Sparkline : Mouse over on dot: On hover of the dots, the data should display e.g. On hover of weight dot 1: 90 lbs, on hover of weight dot 2: 98lbs etc. if goal has not been achieved the goal amount e.g. 90lbs should display in red color; otherwise it should just be in the default black text. (for some reason all hover over text displaying in red currently) Color of the dot changes: yes, if target is achieved dot = green, if target not achieved dot = red. If the dot is achieved: If the dot is not achieved target: Action Plan sparkline dots: Mouse over: on mouseover on the DOT (everywhere), the dot should be black so the user gets visual feedback that that dot is being hovered on. BP sparkline dots: Shows 2 lines, Dots dots: Triangle dots: eNot sure where the triangle dots came from – is this to distinguish diastolic vs systolic? Color change upon mouse over : if target is achieved dot = green, if target not achieved dot = red. Baseline Horizontal line: Take this horizontal line out, we are not going to have this as it is visually difficult to understand the target (baseline) in such a small space. See general suggestion above on gaining more vertical real estate for sparklines. Representing? Date on the score: Date that the vital/outcome was taken. Any Difference on UI like Encounter page, Patient Status(History) sparkline behaviors/ UI. All the same.

UPDATED SPARKLINE SPEC per Sarah Neyaz from e-mail.:

Hi Sarah,
I would like a CM sparkline spec behavior clarification since there has been numerous bugs around CM sparklines.  I think it will be helpful.  (JFYI, attached is patient status flyout mock up from long time ago.)  I wanted to clarify the behavior of sparklines in CM since there have been numerous bug fixes and behavior regressions.  Others feel free to chime in.  Thanks! 
 
QUESTIONS:
Sparkline : Mouse over on dot: On hover of the dots, the data should display e.g. On hover of weight dot 1: 90 lbs, on hover of weight dot 2: 98lbs etc. if goal has not been achieved the goal amount e.g. 90lbs should display in red color; otherwise it should just be in the default black text. (for some reason all hover over text displaying in red currently)
Color of the dot changes: yes, if target is achieved dot = green, if target not achieved  dot = red.
If the dot is achieved:
If the dot is not achieved target:
Action Plan sparkline dots:
Mouse over: on mouseover on the DOT (everywhere), the dot should be black so the user gets visual feedback that that dot is being hovered on.
BP sparkline dots:
Shows 2 lines,
Dots dots:
Triangle dots: eNot sure where the triangle dots came from – is this to distinguish diastolic vs systolic?
Color change upon mouse over :  if target is achieved dot = green, if target not achieved  dot = red.
Baseline Horizontal line: Take this horizontal line out, we are not going to have this as it is visually difficult to understand the target (baseline) in such a small space. See general suggestion above on gaining more vertical real estate for sparklines.
Representing? 
Date on the score: Date that the vital/outcome was taken.
Any Difference on UI like Encounter page, Patient Status(History) sparkline behaviors/ UI. All the same.

event.s:
(from Dale) 7/6
I was actually taking address_episode into account in the ETL postgres query, but was counting on address_episode's encounter_id to be populated, since an episode can only be addressed at encounter time. I found a way to rework the query and it should work correctly once I test it more and check it in. The only patient thus far with out-of-the-box last-addressed problems is Louisa Lee in PCA. We should be able to test this today. Louisa Lee (86 F)

case.sLatestTextSummary: Use Case As a care manager, I would like the ability to add a new patient to care management or edit an existing patient's demographics from care management. Requirements A demographics widget needs to be created that can be launched from within ...
case.sTitle: Requirements Umbrella: Patient Demographics: Launch demographics from within Care Mangement tab

event.s:
Use Case
As a care manager, I would like the ability to add a new patient to care management or edit an existing patient's demographics from care management.
Requirements
A demographics widget needs to be created that can be launched from within the Care Management tab.
Only patient records which exist in the virtual practice can be edited. All other patients cannot be edited from the CM tab (this is because the patient demographics data will likely being overwritten each night by the daily PM feeds)
The demographics widget will contain a limited set of demographics information:
MRN
First Name
Last Name
Gender
Date of Birth
All address information (address line 1,2, city, state, zip)
Insurance drop down (list of insurers)
Insurance: primary/secondary/tertiary
All Contact information
All Legal Guardian information
All Extended Demographics information
New Patient
There needs to be a way to add a new patient
When creating a new patient from within CM, the MRN should auto-generate and it should not be editable.
The new patient entered through the Care Management demographics widget should be stored in the 'Care Management' practice (aka virtual practice).
Editing Patient
Upon initial launch of the patient demographics modal, the modal will be read-only with an 'edit' link. Clicking the edit link will then turn all their fields except MRN to editable.
Editing an existing patient should be easy/seamless (hyperlink all instances of patient's name)
When editing a patient's demographic information, the MRN number should not be editable.
event.sHtml:
Use Case

As a care manager, I would like the ability to add a new patient to care management or edit an existing patient's demographics from care management.

 

Requirements

  1. A demographics widget needs to be created that can be launched from within the Care Management tab.
  2. Only patient records which exist in the virtual practice can be edited. All other patients cannot be edited from the CM tab (this is because the patient demographics data will likely being overwritten each night by the daily PM feeds)
  3. The demographics widget will contain a limited set of demographics information:
  • MRN
  • First Name
  • Last Name
  • Gender
  • Date of Birth
  • All address information (address line 1,2, city, state, zip)
  • Insurance drop down (list of insurers)
  • Insurance: primary/secondary/tertiary
  • All Contact information
  • All Legal Guardian information
  • All Extended Demographics information

New Patient

  1. There needs to be a way to add a new patient
  2. When creating a new patient from within CM, the MRN should auto-generate and it should not be editable.
  3. The new patient entered through the Care Management demographics widget should be stored in the 'Care Management' practice (aka virtual practice).

Editing Patient

  1. Upon initial launch of the patient demographics modal, the modal will be read-only with an 'edit' link. Clicking the edit link will then turn all their fields except MRN to editable.
  2. Editing an existing patient should be easy/seamless (hyperlink all instances of patient's name)
  3. When editing a patient's demographic information, the MRN number should not be editable.

case.sTitle: Reporting: Clinical

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Chaney Jernigan by Allison Thannisch

event.s:
This request is coming from Tawny at Community Hospital (QHN…Grand Valley Primary Care):
Here is the list thus far of my “wish list” for information/data I would love to see extracted from CCR, specific to health coaching: 1. Total coaching appts. per coach/provider/employer/client (should I pull John Doe, can I see that he has been in 5 times?) 2. Time per appt (30 or 60 min) 3. Reason for referral, and whether the referral was self/provider 4. Goals (primary, secondary, etc.), time frame of goal achievement (1, 2, 3 mo), and percentage of goal met at time frame given
It would be great if, over time, we are able to see where we (as a team or individually) are having the most success/behavior change – is it weight loss, diabetic self-care, etc. This could help in identifying how we assign clients to coaches, or who else we may need to recruit for future coaches.
event.sChanges: Member changed from '' to 'QHN' Category changed from 'Bug' to 'Feature'.
event.sHtml:
This request is coming from Tawny at Community Hospital (QHN…Grand Valley Primary Care):

 

Here is the list thus far of my “wish list” for information/data I would love to see extracted from CCR, specific to health coaching:
1.       Total coaching appts. per coach/provider/employer/client (should I pull John Doe, can I see that he has been in 5 times?)
2.       Time per appt (30 or 60 min)
3.       Reason for referral, and whether the referral was self/provider
4.       Goals (primary, secondary, etc.), time frame of goal achievement (1, 2, 3 mo), and percentage of goal met at time frame given
 
It would be great if, over time, we are able to see where we (as a team or individually) are having the most success/behavior change – is it weight loss, diabetic self-care, etc.  This could help in identifying how we assign clients to coaches, or who else we may need to recruit for future coaches.

case.sTitle: Outreach Status: Ability for the member to customize the options for Care Management tab

event.s:
Requirements
Covenant would like the ability to change the options in the dropdown for outreach status on the care management encounter page. Their comment was that it looks like we just used the ones from the Outreach tab in Registry and they may not all be appropriate for what Care Managers do.
Therefore, it makes sense that we would allow the user to customize the outreach status just for the care management tab (and not affect the outreach statuses on the Outreach tab) at a member level.
OPEN ITEMS
Could be done either at the time of implementation by a services team member, or done by the member through an admin UI, or on the fly by any care manager.

case.sTitle: Requirements Umbrella: Assessments

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Chaney Jernigan by Allison Thannisch

event.s:
Requirements
For the first iteration, we are only concerned about the intake grouping and the assessments within it.
We are not going to handle stand-alone assessments or any other grouping or combination of assessments, however, keep in mind that we do eventually want this flexibility. For example, if medication adherence is an assessment within the Intake Grouping, in the future we want the ability for the user to perform the intake assessment once for a patient, but then potentially perform just the medication adherence assessment each month for that patient.
...more to come with the images

For example, if medication adherence is an assessment within the Intake Grouping, in the future we want the ability for the user to perform the intake assessment once for a patient, but then potentially perform just the medication adherence assessment each month for that patient.

case.sTitle: Requirements Umbrella: Self-management Goals

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Chaney Jernigan by Allison Thannisch

event.s:
Use Case
As a care manager, I would like the ability to select self management goals for a patient from a pre-defined list. I would also like the ability to add self management goals to a patient's chart on the fly and not be constrained by the per-defined self management goals.
Requirements
Ability to add free text goals as both the parent and child level
Free text goals will be saved to the patient's record
Free text goals will not persist across the user's session. Meaning if the user entered a free-text self management goal of walking up the stairs for Patient A, if the user then wanted to enter this same goal for Patient B, it would not be in their list to select from, they would have to free-text this in again.
Ability to select a parent self management goal
Ability to select a child self management goal
event.sHtml:
Use Case

As a care manager, I would like the ability to select self management goals for a patient from a pre-defined list. I would also like the ability to add self management goals to a patient's chart on the fly and not be constrained by the per-defined self management goals.

Requirements

Ability to add free text goals as both the parent and child level

  • Free text goals will be saved to the patient's record
  • Free text goals will not persist across the user's session. Meaning if the user entered a free-text self management goal of walking up the stairs for Patient A, if the user then wanted to enter this same goal for Patient B, it would not be in their list to select from, they would have to free-text this in again.

case.sTitle: Requirements Umbrella: Virtual Practice & Automatic / Manual Patient Candidate Nomination

event.s:
Use Case
As a services team member, during member setup, I want to be able to specify if all of the member's 'real' practices (non-virtual) should be setup for automatic care management patient candidates or manual intervention CM patient candidates.
As a services team member, during member setup, I want to be able to flag the 'virtual' practice as such so that the Care Management application and CPRM integration works correctly. (i.e. - patients from the virtual practice are editable in CM, patients sent to this practice from CPRM are automatically marked as candidates in CM).
Requirements
1. Ability for a services team member to set at the member org-level if the practices are automatically or manually nominating patients received from CPRM as Care Manager Candidates
Manually = current implementation, a rule is triggered based on the send from CPRM to CCR that requires a clinician intervention to then get the patient into CM
Automatically = New feature, sending patients from CPRM to CCR automatically nominates the patient as a Candidate in CM. A clinical reminder (rule) is not generated for this patient.
Note: This setting does not apply to the 'virtual' practice.
There is no UI for this feature since this will be done outside of the application (as part of the deployment process)
2. Ability for services team member to flag the 'virtual' practice as such
Nominated patients received from CPRM into the virtual practice are ALWAYS automatically sent as candidates to Care Management regardless of the member org-level setting for automatic/manual CM candidates.
Only patients from the virtual practice can be edited in CM
event.sHtml:
Use Case

As a services team member, during member setup, I want to be able to specify if all of the member's 'real' practices (non-virtual) should be setup for automatic care management patient candidates or manual intervention CM patient candidates.

As a services team member, during member setup, I want to be able to flag the 'virtual' practice as such so that the Care Management application and CPRM integration works correctly. (i.e. - patients from the virtual practice are editable in CM, patients sent to this practice from CPRM are automatically marked as candidates in CM).

Requirements

1. Ability for a services team member to set at the member org-level if the practices are automatically or manually nominating patients received from CPRM as Care Manager Candidates

  • Manually = current implementation, a rule is triggered based on the send from CPRM to CCR that requires a clinician intervention to then get the patient into CM
  • Automatically = New feature, sending patients from CPRM to CCR automatically nominates the patient as a Candidate in CM. A clinical reminder (rule) is not generated for this patient.
  • Note: This setting does not apply to the 'virtual' practice.
  • There is no UI for this feature since this will be done outside of the application (as part of the deployment process)

2. Ability for services team member to flag the 'virtual' practice as such

  •  Nominated patients received from CPRM into the virtual practice are ALWAYS automatically sent as candidates to Care Management regardless of the member org-level setting for automatic/manual CM candidates.
  • Only patients from the virtual practice can be edited in CM

case.sTitle: ETL Patient demographics to .NET real-time

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Chaney Jernigan by Dale Hunscher

event.s:
Estimate is TBD until we decide on scope.
If we cut patient demographics ETL out of SSIS, we eliminate the (probably very unlikely) possibility of colliding updates.
However, if we don't do patient ETL along with everything else, there is a likelihood that the ETL'd data will be inconsistent unless we move everything patient-related from SSIS into a Web Service paradigm.
event.sHtml:

case.sTitle: Patient Data Model: Ability to handle 3 insurances per patient

event.s:
User Story
As a care manager, I would like the ability to see all of my patient's insurance information including all insurances they currently have.
Requirements
We need the ability to handle primary, secondary, and tertiary insurances for a patient. Meaning the ability to store up to three insurances for a patient and specify which one is primary, secondary, tertiary. Each insurance will still contain the standard insurance fields we already handle in the application: Insurance name, policy number, insurance plan rank (primary, secondary, tertiery).
OPEN ITEM:
Currently in CCR - A patient can have more than one primary insurance, this does not seem correct to me however I do not think we can put this restriction into Care Management if CCR does not follow it.
event.sHtml:

case.sTitle: Care Management: Outcomes - Clean up list

event.s:
Goal
The outcomes listed in Care Management should all be applicable outcomes that a care manager/clinician would monitor in order to determine the patient's success in the program.
Requirements
Currently the outcomes listed in Care Management are not all applicable, thus we've come up with this shortened list of Outcomes that should display in the outcomes drop down:
Blood Pressure
BMI
Creatinine Clearance
Ejection Fraction
Hemoglobin A1C
LDL
Peak Flow
Weight
The below strike through text is now in a separate case. See Case 50626
For the below outcomes, the corresponding service codes should be pulled from the lab groups (group name to be added to this case):
Creatinine Clearance
Ejection Fraction
Hemoglobin A1C
LDL
Additionally - all outcomes listed above should have sparkline graphs displayed in Care Management when at least one data point is present for the corresponding service code.
event.sHtml:

Open Questions:
Lab groups could be different from one postgres db to another and Care Management is across all postgres dbs for a given member - which lab group should be used?
For Lab groups - since these could be different from one pg database to another, we want to use 'practice zero' which is the one practice that is defined as the 'standard' for each member. This should be the same practice that is referenced for the CGP report. Please ask Dale for clarifications around the 'practice zero'.
